Usage: vcpe build --manifest <path> [flags]

Resolves image actions (build, pull, or noop) for all services in the manifest without starting any containers. Respects the image pull policy declared in the manifest. Defaults to building a multi-arch OCI manifest list for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64; requires QEMU emulation on the Podman machine for cross-arch targets.

Required flags:
  --manifest <path>       Path to deployment manifest YAML

Optional flags:
  --backend <podman|docker>  Container runtime for image operations (default: podman). With --backend docker, multi-arch builds use `docker buildx build --push` and push to the registry during build.
  --platform <csv>        Comma-separated OS/arch targets (default: linux/amd64,linux/arm64)
  --no-cache              Disable layer cache when building images
  --state-root <path>     Override the default state root directory
  --json                  Emit structured JSON output

Examples:
  vcpe build --manifest manifests/example.yaml
  vcpe build --manifest manifests/example.yaml --backend docker
  vcpe build --manifest manifests/example.yaml --platform linux/amd64
